title: Move saving current card index to async task instead of loader.
message:
Move saving current card index to async task instead of loader.

Loaders are connected to an activity, so if saving index process isn’t
finished it would be done on next activity start, but current index on
activity start would be wrong. Async task has more chances to save
current index at a right time. It has no callbacks or connections to
activity so there would be no trouble to handle it.

Potentially the same thing could be applied for the deletion operations
(delete deck and delete card), I’m not really sure about this.

title: Fix cards pager behaviour after screen rotation.
message:
Fix cards pager behaviour after screen rotation.

After rotation activity is recreated and calls population of pager via
async task loader. Visible page becomes invisible (empty) some strange
way, left-right swipe works fine and shows correct pages. Setting pager
adapter fixes the problem.

Probably a cause of the problem is in pager adapter which saves current
page index for himself and restores it after rotation, but it hasn’t
cards anymore (because they are loading via async task loader). The
thing is that card fragment HAS card object after rotation. This is a
really strange thing, probably issue:
http://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=19211
